The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 June is 42,293 (4,895.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 May, there were 92 new confirmed cases (10.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 May, there were 44 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 109% (48 extra cases).
